& [ProgrammerMergeReviewProtocol] is the planned gate surface for future multi-Programmer outputs
  @ [governing_specification] specifications/Hierarchical_Agent_Swarm.sop
  @ [created_at] 2026-05-29T20:20:00Z

  + [protocol_status] is planned_not_executable
  + [authority_boundary] is merge_review_protocol_surface_not_parallel_execution
  + [use_when] is two_or_more Programmer outputs are produced for one approved code-layer package

  = must: preserve each Programmer output as a separate reviewed artifact before merge
  = must: require Manager review of every ProgrammerReport before accepting merged output
  = must: require Shaliach review when merge changes scope, authority, lineage, data shape, or artifact form
  = must: map merged files back to source work slices and Programmer reports
  = must: keep conflict, overlap, and rejected output visible
  = must: run tests or explicit verification after merge

  - never: silently overwrite one Programmer output with another
  - never: treat assignment claim as merge approval
  - never: apply multi-Programmer patches to the target workspace before merge review and rollback policy exist

& [MergeReviewInputSet] is the required evidence before merge review
  + [input] is ProgrammerAssignmentPlan
  + [input] is WorkSlice for each Programmer
  + [input] is ProgrammerReport for each Programmer
  + [input] is changed file list for each Programmer output
  + [input] is code package authority and Manager approval
  + [input] is ShaliachFinding or no_finding for scope-sensitive outputs

& [MergeConflictLedger] is the conflict surface for future merge review
  + [conflict_type] is same_file_overlap, incompatible_data_shape, duplicated_feature, missing_test, scope_expansion, or unresolved_requirement
  + [required_record] is conflict_type, affected_files, source_programmers, manager_decision, shaliach_finding_ref, and repair_action
  + [resolution] is accept_one, combine_with_rework, request_programmer_rework, defer, or reject

& [MergeAcceptanceGate] is the minimum acceptance condition
  + [required] is all accepted outputs trace to approved work slices
  + [required] is rejected outputs remain visible with reasons
  + [required] is merged result has ManagerReview accepted or request_rework
  + [required] is FileChangeSurface maps merged files to source solution records
  + [required] is verification command result is attached
  + [not_yet_implemented] is executable merge runner
  + [not_yet_implemented] is target-workspace patch application and rollback policy
